#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/patterns-children-over-render-props.md
M|rules|title: Prefer Composing Children Over Render Props
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: cleaner composition, better readability
M|rules|tags: composition, children, render-props
M|rules|Use `children` for composition instead of `renderX` props. Children are more
M|rules|readable, compose naturally, and don't require understanding callback
M|rules|signatures.
M|rules|**Incorrect (render props):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Composer({
M|rules|renderHeader,
M|rules|renderFooter,
M|rules|renderActions,
M|rules|}: {
M|rules|renderHeader?: () => React.ReactNode
M|rules|renderFooter?: () => React.ReactNode
M|rules|renderActions?: () => React.ReactNode
M|rules|}) {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<form>
M|rules|{renderHeader?.()}
M|rules|<Input />
M|rules|{renderFooter ? renderFooter() : <DefaultFooter />}
M|rules|{renderActions?.()}
M|rules|</form>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Usage is awkward and inflexible
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer
M|rules|renderHeader={() => <CustomHeader />}
M|rules|renderFooter={() => (
M|rules|<>
M|rules|<Formatting />
M|rules|<Emojis />
M|rules|</>
M|rules|)}
M|rules|renderActions={() => <SubmitButton />}
M|rules|/>
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (compound components with children):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function ComposerFrame({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|rules|return <form>{children}</form>
M|rules|}
M|rules|function ComposerFooter({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
M|rules|return <footer className='flex'>{children}</footer>
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Usage is flexible
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<Composer.Frame>
M|rules|<CustomHeader />
M|rules|<Composer.Input />
M|rules|<Composer.Footer>
M|rules|<Composer.Formatting />
M|rules|<Composer.Emojis />
M|rules|<SubmitButton />
M|rules|</Composer.Footer>
M|rules|</Composer.Frame>
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**When render props are appropriate:**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|// Render props work well when you need to pass data back
M|rules|<List
M|rules|data={items}
M|rules|renderItem={({ item, index }) => <Item item={item} index={index} />}
M|rules|/>
M|rules|```
M|rules|Use render props when the parent needs to provide data or state to the child.
M|rules|Use children when composing static structure.